Job Description
Under general direction of the Operations Manager, the Helpdesk Support Technician serves as the primary contact for department staff, end-users and vendors in coordinating and resolving service requests and services involving Helpdesk and customer service functions. Performs a variety of duties related to the software assistance of the various systems used by the City.

Essential Functions
Provides first-level support to end-users by researching and answering questions, resolving computer and phone problems;
Records trouble calls into the Helpdesk software, provides follow-up support until problem is resolved or escalated to advanced level support;
Trains and assists City end-users with hardware repair service calls for printers, phones, etc.;
Deploy new computers and devices under the guidance of the Operations Manager;
Assists in the installation of software and hardware as needed;
Assists in monitoring daily, weekly and monthly backups;
Assists end-users with data recovery, such as performing file restores;
Active role in the IT Disaster Recovery preparation and/or disaster recovery efforts, as may be designated in the City Comprehensive Emergency Management Plan
Performs other related duties as assigned.

Knowledge, Skills and Abilities
Knowledge of enterprise backup software;
Working knowledge of network and personal computer hardware and equipment;
Ability to operate tools, components, and peripheral accessories such as printers, and scanners.
Knowledge and practical experience of personal computers, telecommunications and information technology;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite, spreadsheets, word processing, email, and web-based communication;
Ability to communicate technical information to non-technical employees;
Knowledge of computer programming techniques.

Minimum and Preferred Qualifications
EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE:

Any combination of education and experience equivalent to an associate or technical degree from an accredited college or university or related technology support experience. Experience with local or state government preferred, but not required.

Employee must be able to clear a FDLE/CJIS background check and security exam and maintain CJIS certification.

SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS:

Must possess a valid State of Florida Class "E" driver's license.

PHYSICAL DEMANDS:

Must be able to lift, carry and push articles weighing up to 50 lbs. Exposure to electrical hazards, confined spaces, radiation, and moving mechanical parts.

The City of Boca Raton is an Equal Opportunity, Inclusive, Veteran's Preference Employer and Drug Free Workplace. It is the policy of the City of Boca Raton to prohibit discrimination on the basis of race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, marital status, age, national origin, disability, pregnancy, familial status, sexual orientation, genetic information, or any other status or condition protected by applicable federal, state or local laws.
