JOB SUMMARY: The IT Support Specialist I provide support to BestCare staff for a distributed PC/networking environment, including assistance with user general software and hardware questions and needs, tracking incidents and requests for IT support to trouble-shoot, identify and resolve or refer problems according to Health Informatics Director and company protocols.
ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:
1. Serves as primary contact and/or liaison between Velox and BestCare staff needs;
2. Initiates new access to BestCare equipment, networks, applications, and technology. Discontinue all employee access upon separation of employment;
3. Provides Tier I technical, operational, and training support to users either by telephone, email, virtual, or in person hardware and software systems;
4. Tracks and maintain documentation of support service according to protocol;
5. Works with Health Informatics Director and Velox to support on-site networks and server needs;
6. Resolves technical issues timely based on urgency and/or priority;
7. Completes access, changes, and troubleshooting to include (but not limited to):
a. Active Directory (AD) access and changes
b. AD password resets
c. Device and equipment management
d. Network connectivity
e. Microsoft Teams access
g. EHR Software
8. Follows up on any unresolved user problems, outstanding trouble calls, or other areas of concern to be escalated to the Director or Velox for further analysis and support.
9. Receives equipment deliveries from vendors, maintains inventory and accounting for deliveries, assists with updating equipment records and imaging systems;
10. Assists with preparing equipment and delivery to BestCare locations;
11. Assists in procurement of supplies and equipment as directed;
12. Helps develop/maintain documentation protocols and workflows to support staff;
13. Communicates and supports the creation of a ticketing system and user agreements for the distribution and collection of equipment;
14. May be required to travel to other BestCare sites to perform related job functions;
15. Other related duties as assigned.
ORGANIZATIONAL RESPONSIBILITIES:
1. Performs work in alignment with the BestCare’s mission, vision, values;
1. Supports the organization’s commitment to equity, diversity, and inclusion by fostering a culture of open-mindedness, cultural awareness, compassion, and respect for all individuals;
2. Strives to meet annual Program/Department goals and supports the organization’s strategic goals;
3. Adheres to the organization’s Code of Conduct, Business Ethics, Employee Handbook, and all other policies, procedures, and relevant compliance standards;
4. Understands and maintains professionalism and confidentiality per HIPAA, 42 CFR, and Oregon Statutes;
5. Attends required program/staff meetings and completes assigned training timely and satisfactorily;
6. Ensures that any required certifications and/or licenses are kept current and renewed timely;
7. Works independently as well as participates as a positive, collaborative team member;
8. Performs other organizational duties as needed.
QUALIFICATIONS:
EDUCATION AND/OR EXPERIENCE:
High School Diploma (or equivalent) required
LICENSES AND CERTIFICATIONS:
Must maintain a valid Oregon Driver License or ability to obtain one upon hire, and be insurable under the organization’s auto liability coverage policy (minimum 21 years of age and with no Type A violations in the past 3 years, or three (3) or more Type B violations)
Must have reliable transportation to travel between BestCare locations as needed
PREFERRED:
Associates degree in related field preferred
Experience providing basic operating system and application support to users preferred
REQUIRED COMPETENCIES: Must have demonstrated competency or ability to attain competency for each of the following within a reasonable period:
High proficiency in MS Office 365 (Word, Excel, Outlook), databases, virtual meeting platforms, internet, and ability to learn new or updated software;
Knowledge of and skills in PCs/large networks;
Strong communication skills (oral and written);
Demonstrated ability to communicate technical information to audiences of varied levels of technical knowledge and to provide quality service
Excellent interpersonal and customer service skills working with a diverse population of staff;
Strong prioritization skills, follow-through, and excellent attention to detail required;
Excellent time management skills with a proven ability to meet deadlines;
Critical thinking skills
Ability to maintain strict confidence as required by HIPAA, 42 CFR, and Oregon Statutes;
Ability to build and maintain positive relationships;
Ability to function well, remain calm and flexible, and use good judgment in a high-paced and at times stressful environment;
Ability to manage conflict resolution and anger/fear/hostility/violence of others appropriately and effectively;
Ability to work effectively and respectfully in a diverse, multi-cultural environment;
Ability to work independently as well as participating as a positive, collaborative team member;
Ability and willingness to travel between business locations as needed.

TOOLS AND EQUIPMENT USED: Computer/laptop, copy/fax/scanning machines, printer, telephone or multi-line phone.
WORK ENVIRONMENT/PHYSICAL DEMANDS: The work environment is respectful, multi-cultural and inclusive, and the characteristics described above are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. The position requires the employee to dress in a manner that meets the standards for professional attire at Best Care or per department-or job-specific requirements (See Dress Code Policy in Employee Handbook). Other conditions/demands include:
Primarily indoors (95%)
Prolonged periods sitting at a desk and working on a computer/laptop, with occasional standing and walking
Exerts force or lifts/carries up to 10-20 pounds at times
Pushes/pulls 50-75 pounds occasionally
Continuous use of arms, wrists, hands to perform repetitive tasks/motions
Occasional grasping/squeezing and reaching above or below shoulder-level
May occasionally be required to bend, stoop, crawl
Must be able to hear alarms/telephone/audio/normal speaking voice
Must have clarity of vision: Near (<20”); Mid (>20” to < 20’); Far (> 20’)
Must be able to drive motor vehicle to perform job
May be exposed to communicable disease
